text:
Bezirk Spittal an der Drau is an administrative district in Carinthia, Austria. The administrative centre is also named Spittal an der Drau.
The highest point is the peak of the Grossglockner, Austria's highest mountain at. The district also includes Millstätter See and Weissensee, two of the major Carinthian lakes.
Administrative divisions.
The district is divided into 33 municipalities, three of them are towns and nine of them are market towns.
